  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of the present study is to evaluate the a prior hypothesis that treatment with
      icodextrin during acute peritonitis would improve the treatment outcomes of peritonitis
      complicating peritoneal dialysis. The safety and effectiveness of icodextrin for decreasing
      glucose exposure, extent and severity of peritonitis will be evaluated in the setting of
      acute peritonitis complicating peritoneal dialysis among patients who are not receiving
      icodextrin.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
